Three SDL2 SDL_BuildAudioCVT + SDL_ConvertAudio call sites in Pixtone.cpp
become the SDL3 SDL_AudioStream lifecycle: Create / Put / Flush / Get /
Destroy.

Sites:
1. Pixtone::playResampled (was line 372 in upstream): runtime resample
   to a per-rate cache slot when an SFX is requested at a non-cached
   pitch. SAMPLE_RATE → resampled_rate, S16 stereo throughout.
2. Pixtone::prepareResampled (was line 445): pre-cache resample for the
   stream sounds (SND_STREAM1/STREAM2 at predetermined pitch variants;
   called once at SoundManager init for Core battle / SSS in main artery).
3. Pixtone::_prepareToPlay (was line 508): the load-time conversion of
   each Pixtone-rendered SFX from S8 mono 22050 → S16 stereo SAMPLE_RATE.
   Runs once per SFX during sound system init.

The result `Uint8 *sound_buf` still flows into Mix_QuickLoad_RAW unchanged
in this patch; that call becomes MIX_LoadRawAudio in 0014. So 0013 alone
does not produce a compiling tree — it intentionally leaves Mix_*-stuff
in place to keep the patch atomic in concept (CVT migration only) and
small enough to read end-to-end. The 0013-0017 series together compiles.

Audio format constants AUDIO_S8 / AUDIO_S16 (SDL2) → SDL_AUDIO_S8 /
SDL_AUDIO_S16 (SDL3) at the same call sites. Folded into this patch
rather than a separate one because they're touched only here in Pixtone
and are part of the same conceptual migration.

Behavioral correctness reasoning:
- AudioStream's resample math is SDL3's reference implementation; it
  replaces SDL2's SDL_BuildAudioCVT linear-resample at the same input/
  output format pair. For S16-stereo→S16-stereo at integer rate ratios
  the output is byte-identical or trivially close; for the S8-mono-22050
  → S16-stereo-44100 path the format conversion + 2x upsample is the
  same arithmetic in either API.
- No allocation policy change: the converted buffer is still SDL_malloc'd
  for handoff to Mix_QuickLoad_RAW, ownership semantics preserved (RAW
  takes ownership / freed on Mix_FreeChunk).
- Error handling matches the existing style: log SDL_GetError() at each
  step, continue to the next step (the original SDL_BuildAudioCVT/
  SDL_ConvertAudio calls did the same — log + continue).

Per docs/SDL3-MIGRATION.md § 4 (annotate decisions, not substitutions):
no DOS-PORT comments at the call sites. Mechanical SDL2→SDL3 migration
is migration noise; git blame + this commit message tells the story.

Patch 1/4 of the audio refactor's remaining work; foundation is 0017
(landed); 0014 (Pixtone Mix_*→MIX_* + 64-track pool) and 0015 (Organya
HookMusic→TrackRawCallback + S16→float boundary) and 0016 (Ogg) follow.
